comments.body:
Loading the entire dataset too 266 seconds just to grab the AWS objects
```
def load_all_data
  bucket_name = "prds-dataspace"
  prefix = "10-34770/8ecv-zm19/"
  client = Work.new().s3_client
  start_time = DateTime.now
  resp = client.list_objects_v2({ bucket: bucket_name, max_keys: 1000, prefix: })
  responses = [resp]
  while resp.is_truncated do
    token = resp.next_continuation_token
    resp = client.list_objects_v2({ bucket: bucket_name, max_keys: 1000, prefix:, continuation_token: token })
    responses << resp
  end
  end_time = DateTime.now
  puts "It took #{end_time.to_i - start_time.to_i}"
  responses
end
```
It took 646 number of seconds to load the S3Files
``` 
def load_objects
  bucket_name = "prds-dataspace"
  prefix = "10-34770/8ecv-zm19/"
  client = Work.new().s3_client
  start_time = DateTime.now
  resp = client.list_objects_v2({ bucket: bucket_name, max_keys: 1000, prefix: })
   objects = parse_objects(resp, ignore_directories: false)
  result_objects  = objects
  while resp.is_truncated do
    token = resp.next_continuation_token
    resp = client.list_objects_v2({ bucket: bucket_name, max_keys: 1000, prefix:, continuation_token: token })
   objects = parse_objects(resp, ignore_directories: false)
    result_objects += objects
  end
  end_time = DateTime.now
  puts "It took #{end_time.to_i - start_time.to_i}"
  result_objects
end
```
